<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 23 at 4:52PM MST  by NWS Missoula</headline>
<description>...Intense snow showers will impact portions of Deer Lodge, east
central Granite, Silver Bow and southeastern Powell Counties through
615 PM MST...
At 448 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking a line of intense snow
showers along a strong cold front, moving over the Interstate 90
corridor near Drummond.  The front will impact all locations along
the interstate to Butte.  As well as Montana 1 and Highway 12 to
MacDonald Pass. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Visibility one-half mile or less and winds in excess of 40
mph.
IMPACT...Low visibility could result in dangerous driving
conditions.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
